{"id":19455,"date":"2014-07-05T18:10:39","date_gmt":"2014-07-05T14:10:39","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/www.dailyhadithonline.com\/?p=19455"},"modified":"2021-01-29T23:06:53","modified_gmt":"2021-01-29T19:06:53","slug":"hatim-pray-so-well","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2014\/07\/05\/hatim-pray-so-well\/","title":{"rendered":"Hatim on Salat: How do you pray so well?"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Rabah ibn al-Harawi reported: &#8216;Isam ibn Yusuf passed by Hatim al-Asamm, may Allah have mercy on him, while he was speaking in his assembly. &#8216;Isam said, \u201cO Hatim, do you pray well?\u201d Hatim said yes. &#8216;Isam said, \u201cHow do you pray?\u201d Hatim said, \u201cI establish the command, I walk with fear, I begin prayer with intention, I exalt Allah with grandeur, I recite with a measured recitation and reflection, I bow with reverence, I prostrate with humility, I sit to complete the testimony, and I invoke peace properly and according to the Sunnah. Then, I sincerely surrender the prayer to Allah Almighty and I return to myself with fear that it will not be accepted from me. I guard it with effort in this way until death.\u201d &#8216;Isam said, \u201cYou may speak, for you do pray well.\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: H\u0323ilyat al-Awliya\u0304&#8217; 11623<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right\">\u0639\u0646 \u0631\u064e\u0628\u064e\u0627\u062d \u0628\u0652\u0646 \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0647\u064e\u0631\u064e\u0648\u0650\u064a\u0651\u0650 \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0645\u064e\u0631\u0651\u064e \u0639\u0650\u0635\u064e\u0627\u0645\u064f \u0628\u0652\u0646\u064f \u064a\u064f\u0648\u0633\u064f\u0641\u064e \u0628\u0650\u062d\u064e\u0627\u062a\u0650\u0645\u064d \u0627\u0644\u0623\u064e\u0635\u064e\u0645\u0651\u064f \u0631\u062d\u0645\u0647 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647 \u0648\u064e\u0647\u064f\u0648\u064e \u064a\u064e\u062a\u064e\u0643\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0645\u064f \u0641\u0650\u064a \u0645\u064e\u062c\u0